            <entry xml:id="entry_arkʼaw" xml:lang="os-x-iron">
                <form xml:id="form_d2901e66" type="lemma"><orth>arkʼaw</orth></form>
                <usg><lang/></usg>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d2901e72"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>клещи</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>pincers</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Происхождение не ясно. Может быть, из <hi rendition="#rend_italic">*a-krau</hi>, где <hi rendition="#rend_italic">krau</hi>
                    -— к <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2901e136" xml:id="mentioned_d2901e84" xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>claudo</w>
                        <gloss><q>запирать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2901e144" xml:id="mentioned_d2901e92" xml:lang="la"><w>clavis</w>
                        <gloss><q>ключ</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2901e150" xml:id="mentioned_d2901e98" xml:lang="la"><w>clavus</w>
                        <gloss><q>гвоздь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2901e156" xml:id="mentioned_d2901e104" xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>клюка</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2901e161" xml:id="mentioned_d2901e109" xml:lang="ru"><w>ключ</w></mentioned> и
                    пр. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Walde"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">изд.
                            3-е, стр. 229 сл.</biblScope></bibl>). C другой стороны, конечное <hi rendition="#rend_italic">-aw</hi> может быть
                    суффиксом, и тогда приходим к корню <hi rendition="#rend_italic">*ark</hi>, который распознается в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arx"/> ‘сук’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æǧnæg"/> ‘застежка’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxkænyn"/> ‘запирать’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærxæg"/> ‘сустав’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxtong"/> ‘подпруга’ (см. эти слова). Появление
                    смычно-гортанного <hi rendition="#rend_italic">kʼ</hi> вместо <hi rendition="#rend_italic">x</hi> может быть результатом представления о
                    физическом усилии, сопутствующем понятию „клещи“ (см. по этому поводу <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>518–525</biblScope></bibl>).</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">The etymology is not cleat. May be derived from <hi rendition="#rend_italic">*a-krau</hi>, where
                    <hi rendition="#rend_italic">krau</hi> is related to <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2901e84" xml:id="mentioned_d2901e136" xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>claudo</w>
                        <gloss><q>lock</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2901e92" xml:id="mentioned_d2901e144" xml:lang="la"><w>clavis</w>
                        <gloss><q>key</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2901e98" xml:id="mentioned_d2901e150" xml:lang="la"><w>clavus</w>
                        <gloss><q>nail</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2901e104" xml:id="mentioned_d2901e156" xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>kljuka</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d2901e109" xml:id="mentioned_d2901e161" xml:lang="ru"><w>ključ</w></mentioned>
                    etc. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Walde"/><biblScope xml:lang="en">3rd ed., p. 229
                            ff.</biblScope></bibl>). On the other hand, the final <hi rendition="#rend_italic">-aw</hi> may be a
                    suffix, so we come to the stem <hi rendition="#rend_italic">*ark</hi>, which is identified in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arx"/> ‘brach’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æǧnæg"/>
                    ‘fastener’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxkænyn"/> ‘lock’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærxæg"/> ‘joint’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxtong"/>
                    ‘(saddle-)girth’ (see these words). The appearance of the ejective <hi rendition="#rend_italic">kʼ</hi>
                    instead of <hi rendition="#rend_italic">x</hi> may be the result of the idea of physical effort accompanying
                    the concept of ‘pincers’ (see <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>518–525</biblScope></bibl> about this).</etym>
            </entry>
